The failure of the rack and pinion steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or stuck, making it challenging to control the vehicle, especially in cold weather conditions, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel makes a knocking noise
the steering wheel freezes up in cold weather
